<graph edgedefault="undirected"><node id="&quot;ELTON&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Elton argues that size is the main determinant in the structure of the food chain, suggesting expertise in biological or ecological systems."&lt;SEP&gt;"Elton is a medical officer and mountaineer who suffers from illness during the voyage and is assisted by Tom Longstaff."&lt;SEP&gt;"Elton is a member of the expedition team, working alongside botanist Vincent Summerhayes to survey plants and other animals."&lt;SEP&gt;"Elton is a naturalist who documented 'Periodic Fluctuations in Numbers of Animals' and wrote a foundational book on animal ecology in 1924."&lt;SEP&gt;"Elton is a researcher who developed the concept of food chains and their economic connections in animal societies."&lt;SEP&gt;"Elton is a young individual who embarked on a natural history expedition, starting a diary at age thirteen and demonstrating a strong passion for natural history."&lt;SEP&gt;"Elton is the author of a book on the new science of ecology, emphasizing the sociology and economics of animals and their interactions within communities."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9abbae2491bce850b402a75e7a7be8cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6f20e95f2b687a8963c77f9d1f946da0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-20e38e48ffc37fb717229a5dc03ff3a9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c3eb78a029c96288b495cbd85393985&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8cac479cb6cdd8c93500916fa7e3e364&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6dcaa3fb65de0bc40334b1db91763464&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ea2773625d5843544521f09f0155b29</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 27}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 105}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;JULIAN HUXLEY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Julian Huxley is an eminent zoologist and writer who invited Elton on the expedition and was impressed by his student's passion for natural history."&lt;SEP&gt;"Julian Huxley was a former tutor of Elton and proposed for Elton to write a short book on animal ecology for a series of biology books."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4c3eb78a029c96288b495cbd85393985&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8cac479cb6cdd8c93500916fa7e3e364</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 27}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 106}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ARCTIC&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Arctic refers to the region where Elton had three expeditions, contributing to his extensive experience."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Arctic is a geographical location where Elton conducted studies on animal communities, highlighting the importance of food and food chains."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4c3eb78a029c96288b495cbd85393985&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6f20e95f2b687a8963c77f9d1f946da0</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 21}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 103}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ANIMAL ECOLOGY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Animal Ecology is the title of Elton's book, which laid the foundation for the new science of ecology."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4c3eb78a029c96288b495cbd85393985</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;_ANIMAL ECOLOGY_&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"_Animal Ecology_ is the book written by Elton, focusing on animal ecology and setting the agenda for the new science of ecology."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4c3eb78a029c96288b495cbd85393985</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 27}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 106}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LIFE IS ALL ABOUT FOOD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"This phrase represents a principle or idea that Elton explored in his work on animal ecology."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4c3eb78a029c96288b495cbd85393985</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 27}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 105}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OXFORD'S UNIVERSITY MUSEUM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Oxford's University Museum is the location where Elton worked on his book, indicating his academic environment."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4c3eb78a029c96288b495cbd85393985</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 27}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 105}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PERIODIC FLUCTUATIONS IN NUMBERS OF ANIMALS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Periodic Fluctuations in Numbers of Animals is a phenomenon Elton documented in his 1924 paper."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4c3eb78a029c96288b495cbd85393985</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 27}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 105}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SHORT BOOKS ON BIOLOGY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Short books on biology is a series of books that Julian Huxley was putting together, proposing a book on animal ecology for this series."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4c3eb78a029c96288b495cbd85393985</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 27}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 106}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;200-PAGE BOOK&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The 200-page book is a comprehensive work on the new science of ecology, written in an engaging, conversational tone with logical organization around key ideas."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6f20e95f2b687a8963c77f9d1f946da0</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 21}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 103}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CARL LINNAEUS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Carl Linnaeus was a great naturalist in the eighteenth century who embraced the concept of an 'economy of nature,' which influenced Elton's work."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6f20e95f2b687a8963c77f9d1f946da0</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 27}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 105}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DARWIN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Charles Darwin, in the nineteenth century, also embraced the concept of an 'economy of nature,' contributing to the foundation of Elton's ideas."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6f20e95f2b687a8963c77f9d1f946da0</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 27}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 105}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SOCIOLOGY AND ECONOMICS OF ANIMALS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The concept of the sociology and economics of animals refers to the organized structure and economic principles governing animal communities, as discussed in Elton's book."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6f20e95f2b687a8963c77f9d1f946da0</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ECONOMY OF NATURE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The concept of an 'economy of nature' is a biological principle that compares the organization and economic laws of animal communities to those of human societies, as used by both Linnaeus and Darwin."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6f20e95f2b687a8963c77f9d1f946da0</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FOOD AND FOOD CHAINS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Food and food chains are central concepts in Elton's work, representing the primary driving force and currency of animal economies, respectively."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6f20e95f2b687a8963c77f9d1f946da0</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ENGAGING, CONVERSATIONAL TONE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The engaging, conversational tone of the book makes it accessible and easy to read, enhancing the reader's understanding of complex ideas."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6f20e95f2b687a8963c77f9d1f946da0</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 21}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 104}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LOGICAL ORGANIZATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Logical organization of the book's chapters around key ideas helps readers understand and follow the development of Elton's arguments."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6f20e95f2b687a8963c77f9d1f946da0</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 21}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 104}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;KEY IDEAS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Key ideas in the book introduce and set the agenda for major facets of the new science of ecology, providing a structured framework for understanding animal communities."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6f20e95f2b687a8963c77f9d1f946da0</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 21}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 104}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MAJOR FACETS OF ECOLOGY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Major facets of ecology include the sociology and economics of animals, which are central themes in Elton's book."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6f20e95f2b687a8963c77f9d1f946da0</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 21}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 104}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ANIMAL COMMUNITIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Animal communities are the subject of Elton's research and the focus of his book, highlighting their complexity and organization."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6f20e95f2b687a8963c77f9d1f946da0</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 21}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 104}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COMPLEX SOCIETY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The complex society of animals, similar to human society, is a key concept in Elton's work, emphasizing the organized nature of animal groups."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6f20e95f2b687a8963c77f9d1f946da0</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 21}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 104}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ECONOMIC LAWS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Economic laws apply to animal communities, just as they do to human societies, according to Elton's analogy."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6f20e95f2b687a8963c77f9d1f946da0</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 21}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 104}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SIMPLE COMMUNITIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Simple communities are the basis for Elton's analysis, allowing him to identify general principles that can be applied to more complex systems."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6f20e95f2b687a8963c77f9d1f946da0</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 21}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 104}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FOOD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Food is a critical resource for animals, serving as the primary driving force and currency in their economies, as emphasized by Elton."&lt;SEP&gt;"Food is the primary resource and 'currency' in animal economies, driving the activities and survival of all animals."&lt;SEP&gt;"Food is the substance being studied in Cannon's experiments, particularly its movement through the digestive tract."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6f20e95f2b687a8963c77f9d1f946da0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9abbae2491bce850b402a75e7a7be8cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b60c4a915bc63a445da3fc657d962949</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 21}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 104}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FOOD CHAINS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Food chains represent the interconnectedness of animals in their ecosystems, forming the basis of Elton's analysis of animal communities."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6f20e95f2b687a8963c77f9d1f946da0</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 21}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 104}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ANIMAL ECONOMY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Animal Economy refers to the system where animals depend on food for survival and social structure."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9abbae2491bce850b402a75e7a7be8cb</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HERBIVORES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Herbivores are the primary class in animal society, consuming plants and forming the base of food chains."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9abbae2491bce850b402a75e7a7be8cb</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 22}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CARNIVORES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Carnivores are the next class in the food chain, preying on herbivores and forming higher levels of the food chain."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9abbae2491bce850b402a75e7a7be8cb</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 22}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FOOD CHAIN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Food Chain represents the interconnectedness of animals based on their feeding habits, with all organisms ultimately dependent on plants."&lt;SEP&gt;"Food chain is the ecological concept discussed, describing the relationships between organisms based on the transfer of energy and nutrients."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9abbae2491bce850b402a75e7a7be8cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ea2773625d5843544521f09f0155b29</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 22}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SIZE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Size is a critical factor determining what animals can consume in the food chain, with larger animals unable to eat smaller prey and vice versa."&lt;SEP&gt;"Size is a critical factor determining what animals can consume in the food chain, with larger animals unable to subdue or support smaller prey and vice versa."&lt;SEP&gt;"Size is a critical factor in determining what can be eaten or supported in the food chain, as discussed by Elton."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9abbae2491bce850b402a75e7a7be8cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ea2773625d5843544521f09f0155b29</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 22}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SMALL FISH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Small Fish are part of the food chain, consumed by larger fish."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9abbae2491bce850b402a75e7a7be8cb</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 26}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WATER INSECTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Water Insects are part of the food chain, consumed by small fish."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9abbae2491bce850b402a75e7a7be8cb</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 26}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PLANTS AND MUD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Plants and Mud form the base of the food chain, consumed by water insects."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9abbae2491bce850b402a75e7a7be8cb</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 26}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LARGE FOWL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Large Fowl are part of the food chain, consuming larger grains."&lt;SEP&gt;"Large fowl refers to a type of animal that cannot eat small grain, indicating a specific category within the food chain."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9abbae2491bce850b402a75e7a7be8cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ea2773625d5843544521f09f0155b29</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 24}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SMALL GRAIN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Small Grain is part of the food chain, consumed by smaller animals."&lt;SEP&gt;"Small grain is mentioned as something that large fowl cannot eat, implying a specific type of food item in the context of the food chain."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9abbae2491bce850b402a75e7a7be8cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ea2773625d5843544521f09f0155b29</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 24}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Intellectual Property includes various types of rights such as patents, trademarks, trade secrets, copyrights, and domain names, indicating legal and business concepts."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9ea2773625d5843544521f09f0155b29</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 14}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PATENTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Patents are a form of intellectual property right, providing exclusive rights to an invention."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9ea2773625d5843544521f09f0155b29</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 14}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TRADEMARKS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Trademarks are a form of intellectual property right, used to identify and distinguish goods or services."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9ea2773625d5843544521f09f0155b29</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 14}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TRADE SECRETS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Trade Secrets are confidential information that provides a business with a competitive advantage."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9ea2773625d5843544521f09f0155b29</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 14}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COPYRIGHTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Copyrights are a form of intellectual property right, protecting original works of authorship."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9ea2773625d5843544521f09f0155b29</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 14}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INTERNET DOMAIN NAMES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Internet domain names are unique identifiers for websites and online resources."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9ea2773625d5843544521f09f0155b29</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 14}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DEBTORS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Debtors are the entities required to file the Plan Supplement."&lt;SEP&gt;"Debtors refer to parties who owe money or other obligations, in the context of financial agreements."&lt;SEP&gt;"Debtors refer to the entities that are obligated to consummate the Transactions and perform their obligations under the Agreement."&lt;SEP&gt;"Debtors refer to the parties involved in the agreement and are responsible for certain obligations and actions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Debtors refer to the parties involved in the agreement, responsible for supplies, inventories, and the business operations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7a147f7c459c31c557d67f845e41b10e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7c31a02bac8a4cec57c27f54aacd8d10&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-086a5068bbc473cc9788d46b3609f100&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ea2773625d5843544521f09f0155b29&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d490e69c3b4e25af388c35f68d9a7d0c</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 34}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BANKERS’ ACCEPTANCES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bankers’ acceptances are financial instruments issued by banks, often used in international trade."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9ea2773625d5843544521f09f0155b29</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 34}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SWAPS, OPTIONS, DERIVATIVES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Swaps, options, and derivatives are financial instruments used for risk management and speculation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9ea2773625d5843544521f09f0155b29</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 34}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HEDGING AGREEMENTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Hedging agreements are financial contracts used to reduce exposure to price fluctuations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9ea2773625d5843544521f09f0155b29</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 34}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CARNIVOROUS ANIMALS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Carnivorous animals are part of the food chain and determine the upper limit of prey size based on their strength and ability."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9ea2773625d5843544521f09f0155b29</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 27}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 105}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PREY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Prey refers to the animals that are hunted or consumed by predators in the food chain."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9ea2773625d5843544521f09f0155b29</data>
