<node id="&quot;MATERIAL ADVERSE EFFECT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Material Adverse Effect is a term used to describe significant negative impacts on the company's operations or ability to fulfill obligations."&lt;SEP&gt;"Material Adverse Effect is defined as any event, change, effect, condition, state of facts or occurrence that has a material adverse effect on the business, results of operations, financial condition, assets, or liabilities of the Company and its Subsidiaries, or on the ability of the Debtors to consummate the Transactions or perform their obligations under the Agreement."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-086a5068bbc473cc9788d46b3609f100&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7a147f7c459c31c557d67f845e41b10e</data>
</node>
