</node>
<node id="&quot;FEMALE BELT SINGING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Female Belt Singing is a technique involving female chest register sung in the octave above middle C and higher, characterized by brightness, brassiness, fullness, and loudness. It is an extension of the speaking voice and is used in musical performances."&lt;SEP&gt;"Female Belt Singing refers to a specific vocal technique used by female singers, particularly in musical theater, characterized by higher pitches and a distinct style."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e4031c3b36282f451cd6ca67a01df325&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42e78df8d9ca72390c59785d98c0c246</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 13}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 77}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CHEST REGISTER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Chest Register is the lowest register of the speaking voice, created by the thicker part of the vocal folds: the thyroarytenoid (TA) muscle. It is used for speaking and forms the basis of belt singing."&lt;SEP&gt;"Chest register is a vocal range that produces a lower-pitched sound, typically used in music theater."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-42e78df8d9ca72390c59785d98c0c246&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-131ad68d8de95c0e17c0df4f0767988a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 1}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 31}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;THYROARYTENOID (TA) MUSCLE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Thyroarytenoid (TA) Muscle is a part of the vocal folds responsible for creating the chest register, which is essential for producing the speaking and singing voice."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-42e78df8d9ca72390c59785d98c0c246</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 13}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 77}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MIDDLE C&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Middle C is a musical note used as a reference point in music, located in the middle of the piano keyboard and often used as a starting point for vocal ranges."&lt;SEP&gt;"Middle C is a specific musical note used as a reference point in music, marking the starting point for Female Belt Singing."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-42e78df8d9ca72390c59785d98c0c246</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 13}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 77}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HIGH BELT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"High Belt describes belt singing between C4 and above, which is a specific range within the belt voice."</data>
