<node id="&quot;CLASSICAL SINGING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Classical Singing is a form of singing that is characterized by its traditional legit sound, featuring a darker quality and classical resonance."&lt;SEP&gt;"Classical Singing is a style of singing that does not predominantly use the chest register in the C5 octave and above, contrasting with the belt singing technique."&lt;SEP&gt;"Classical singing is a traditional vocal style characterized by specific techniques and qualities, often contrasted with pop/rock and mix styles."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-34c4fa424382a8057d9f53c5dd06fa61&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42e78df8d9ca72390c59785d98c0c246&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7c06928a937cd39c8474e5c5ab0f168a</data>
