<node id="&quot;PHARYNX&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pharynx is a part of the throat involved in vocal production, particularly in the belt technique."&lt;SEP&gt;"Pharynx is the part of the throat that can be soothed by the warmth of tea."&lt;SEP&gt;"Pharynx is the part of the throat that remains in the speech position during male belt singing, not expanding during the high passaggio."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-770756a346b8a35323e1beddd87ca5e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f2370a2f0c089c5553f3263304da90f0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e4031c3b36282f451cd6ca67a01df325</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 15}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 85}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 136}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VOWELS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vowels are not covered or modified during male belt singing, maintaining a clear and speech-oriented sound."&lt;SEP&gt;"Vowels are sounds produced by the mouth and throat, often modified in different vocal techniques."</data>
