<node id="&quot;PARENT COLONY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A parent colony of honey bees is the source from which swarming occurs, splitting into a new colony."&lt;SEP&gt;"Parent Colony is a bee colony that has been weakened and may struggle to survive, and is considering swarming to propagate the species."&lt;SEP&gt;"Parent Colony is the original bee colony from which the swarm originates, containing the queen and worker bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-09cbaf7a9ca024f19e538f5052c7e02b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b8998c07aafc0d539e88b3e51f159fe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-21b0db176175776d50cdbbd4696b062b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 62}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;QUEEN BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Queen Bee is a crucial figure in the bee colony, responsible for laying eggs and maintaining colony morale. She has specific physical characteristics and behaviors distinct from worker bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"Queen Bee is the reproductive female in the bee colony, responsible for laying eggs and initiating the swarm process."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-21b0db176175776d50cdbbd4696b062b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81ecf165e861b9b15f524411477efffe</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 64}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bees are a group of insects that form a colony and work together to maintain the hive, produce honey, and care for the queen."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are insects that collect nectar and produce honey, and they must secrete additional wax and build comb to construct their hives."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are mentioned as not having gotten to the outside yet, suggesting they are a factor in the environment."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are social insects living in colonies, with roles including workers, drones, and queens."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are the primary subject of discussion, focusing on their life cycle, population growth, and challenges faced during the active season."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are the worker insects that form the core of the package colony, responsible for various tasks including pollination and defense."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are the workers of the hive responsible for various tasks such as cleaning, feeding, and maintaining the colony."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are the workers, drones, and the queen of the hive, performing various tasks essential for the colony's survival."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees refer to the worker bees and drones in the hive, collectively forming the colony and performing various tasks such as foraging and protecting the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-894b591a83b914f8f6e97ef8a4c38432&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f2370a2f0c089c5553f3263304da90f0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ee60400c3602b512e18748159440dc7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a5249d7cd72cb7719eac165e812133b7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bcf0c4fe6d9ae7f0f1e8ab75dc1eb4e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-21b0db176175776d50cdbbd4696b062b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3d3ced570c1e921fa39196db14c81607&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cd3280f423032e87d8241124c131edc6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-694253136982b7320b8099c8f3c852c7</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 58}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 127}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SWARM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Swarm is a process where a portion of the bee colony leaves the hive to find a new home, typically initiated by the queen bee."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-21b0db176175776d50cdbbd4696b062b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 63}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LATE SPRING AND EARLY SUMMER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Late Spring and Early Summer are the primary swarm seasons, lasting for about 6 weeks, during which about 80 percent of the swarms occur."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-21b0db176175776d50cdbbd4696b062b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 63}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;AUGUST&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"August marks the beginning of the secondary swarm season, which lasts for about a month and accounts for the remaining 20 percent of swarms."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-21b0db176175776d50cdbbd4696b062b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 63}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LOCAL BEEKEEPERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Local Beekeepers are individuals or groups knowledgeable about beekeeping practices and can provide information about swarm seasons in specific areas."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-21b0db176175776d50cdbbd4696b062b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 63}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PRIMARY SWARM SEASON&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Primary Swarm Season is the main period for swarming, occurring in late spring and early summer, lasting about 6 weeks."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-21b0db176175776d50cdbbd4696b062b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 63}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SECONDARY SWARM SEASON&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Secondary Swarm Season is a less well-known period for swarming, occurring in August, lasting about a month."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-21b0db176175776d50cdbbd4696b062b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 63}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SURVIVAL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Survival refers to the ability of the swarm or the parent colony to endure and thrive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-21b0db176175776d50cdbbd4696b062b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 62}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WINTER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Winter is a period when drones do not survive, marking the end of their active season."&lt;SEP&gt;"Winter is mentioned as a critical time when the parent colony needs to be reestablished and survive."&lt;SEP&gt;"Winter is mentioned as a season, possibly affecting the bees' behavior and the decision to swarm."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-09cbaf7a9ca024f19e538f5052c7e02b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-21b0db176175776d50cdbbd4696b062b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-31552e12186e5af657ecc15691569829</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 67}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;REESTABLISHMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Reestablishment is the process by which the parent colony regains its strength after a swarm."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-21b0db176175776d50cdbbd4696b062b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 62}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FORAGING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Foraging is the activity performed by worker bees to gather food for the colony."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-21b0db176175776d50cdbbd4696b062b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 58}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 126}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PROTECTING THE HIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Protecting the Hive is the activity performed by worker bees and drones to safeguard the colony."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-21b0db176175776d50cdbbd4696b062b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 58}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 127}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PROPAGATING THE SPECIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Propagating the Species is the general reason for swarming, which is to ensure the continuation of the bee population."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-21b0db176175776d50cdbbd4696b062b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 63}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SWARMING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Swarming is the process by which a bee colony splits into two, typically due to overcrowding or the age of the queen, and involves the formation of a new colony led by a new queen."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-09cbaf7a9ca024f19e538f5052c7e02b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 88}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NEW COLONY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"New Colony is a new bee colony formed during the swarming process, led by a new queen."&lt;SEP&gt;"New colony is another term for the package colony, emphasizing its recent establishment and need for careful management."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-09cbaf7a9ca024f19e538f5052c7e02b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3d3ced570c1e921fa39196db14c81607</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;QUEEN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Queen is a female bee that plays a crucial role in the colony, laying eggs and maintaining the genetic continuity of the hive."&lt;SEP&gt;"Queen is the female bee responsible for laying eggs and maintaining the genetic continuity of the colony."&lt;SEP&gt;"Queen is the reproductive female bee in the hive responsible for laying eggs."&lt;SEP&gt;"Queen is the reproductive female of the bee colony, responsible for laying eggs and mating with drones."&lt;SEP&gt;"Queen refers to the female bee responsible for laying eggs, crucial for the colony's survival and growth."&lt;SEP&gt;"Queen refers to the female bee that lays eggs and is central to the survival and propagation of the colony."&lt;SEP&gt;"queen refers to the female reproductive bee in the hive, crucial for laying eggs and maintaining the colony."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-894b591a83b914f8f6e97ef8a4c38432&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ee60400c3602b512e18748159440dc7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a5249d7cd72cb7719eac165e812133b7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-09cbaf7a9ca024f19e538f5052c7e02b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-31552e12186e5af657ecc15691569829&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3d3ced570c1e921fa39196db14c81607&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-694253136982b7320b8099c8f3c852c7</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 59}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 128}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Hive is referred to as a place to be visited meaningfully, implying it holds some significance or importance."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is the living space of the bee colony, where they store honey, raise brood, and live."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is the structure built by bees using wax, which serves as their home and storage for honey."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is the structure where the colony lives and performs its activities."&lt;SEP&gt;"hive is the living space of the bee colony, consisting of frames with comb and a queen."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-09cbaf7a9ca024f19e538f5052c7e02b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-31552e12186e5af657ecc15691569829&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cd3280f423032e87d8241124c131edc6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-694253136982b7320b8099c8f3c852c7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d490e69c3b4e25af388c35f68d9a7d0c</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 61}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OUTER COVER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Outer Cover is a part of the hive equipment used to protect the bees and allow access for inspection or treatment."&lt;SEP&gt;"Outer Cover is the top part of the beehive that protects the hive body and the bees inside."&lt;SEP&gt;"Outer cover is the topmost part of the hive that protects the bees and the internal structures from the elements."&lt;SEP&gt;"outer cover is the topmost layer of the hive, providing protection from the elements."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-09cbaf7a9ca024f19e538f5052c7e02b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-894b591a83b914f8f6e97ef8a4c38432&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-694253136982b7320b8099c8f3c852c7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ee60400c3602b512e18748159440dc7</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 61}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FEEDER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Feeder is a container used to provide additional food sources for the bees, typically placed on the hive to ensure they have enough nutrition."&lt;SEP&gt;"Feeder is a container used to provide food to the bees, typically placed in the hive to ensure they have enough resources."&lt;SEP&gt;"Feeder is a container used to provide food to the bees, typically placed inside the hive."&lt;SEP&gt;"feeder is a container used to provide food to the bees, typically placed inside the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-09cbaf7a9ca024f19e538f5052c7e02b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-894b591a83b914f8f6e97ef8a4c38432&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-694253136982b7320b8099c8f3c852c7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ee60400c3602b512e18748159440dc7</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 58}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 127}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INNER COVER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Inner Cover is a protective layer between the outer cover and the frames of the hive."&lt;SEP&gt;"Inner Cover is a removable layer between the hive body and the outer cover, used to regulate temperature and access the frames."&lt;SEP&gt;"Inner cover is a protective layer between the outer cover and the frames, providing a buffer and preventing direct contact between the two."&lt;SEP&gt;"inner cover is a protective layer placed between the top of the hive body and the outer cover."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-09cbaf7a9ca024f19e538f5052c7e02b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-894b591a83b914f8f6e97ef8a4c38432&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-694253136982b7320b8099c8f3c852c7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ee60400c3602b512e18748159440dc7</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 61}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SMOKER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Smoker is a tool used to calm bees by creating smoke, allowing beekeepers to inspect or manipulate the hive without immediate aggression from the bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"Smoker is a tool used to check if it is still burning, likely for safety purposes."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-09cbaf7a9ca024f19e538f5052c7e02b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d490e69c3b4e25af388c35f68d9a7d0c</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 64}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SMOKE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Smoke is the product of burning materials used to calm bees during hive inspections."&lt;SEP&gt;"Smoke is used to calm bees during the process of inspecting the hive, allowing the bees to realize they have been smoked and reducing agitation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Smoke is used to calm the bees during the installation process."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-894b591a83b914f8f6e97ef8a4c38432&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ee60400c3602b512e18748159440dc7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3d3ced570c1e921fa39196db14c81607</data>
