</node>
<node id="&quot;CANDY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Candy is used as a food source for bees and is placed in the hive to provide sustenance."&lt;SEP&gt;"Candy is used as a food source to feed the bees and encourage the queen to be released from her cage."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8ee60400c3602b512e18748159440dc7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3d3ced570c1e921fa39196db14c81607</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 59}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 129}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEE SPACE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bee space is the optimal distance between combs and other structures within the hive, allowing bees to move freely and build comb without obstruction."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8ee60400c3602b512e18748159440dc7</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 60}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 131}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WILD COMB&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Wild comb is comb built by bees in areas of the hive where it is not intended, often due to the presence of a queen cage or other obstructions."&lt;SEP&gt;"wild comb refers to unmanaged honeycomb structures within a beehive, often problematic due to the presence of queen eggs and potential for bridging frames."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-694253136982b7320b8099c8f3c852c7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ee60400c3602b512e18748159440dc7</data>
