</node>
<node id="&quot;BROOD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Brood refers to the developing bees within the comb, including eggs, larvae, and pupae."&lt;SEP&gt;"Brood refers to the developing young of the hive, including eggs, larvae, and pupae, which are cared for by worker bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"Brood refers to the early developmental stage of an organism, specifically mentioned in the context of castes."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a5249d7cd72cb7719eac165e812133b7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65433026bd213bdc7f57a14af8a9a25f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ee60400c3602b512e18748159440dc7</data>
