</node>
<node id="&quot;FRAMES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Frames are the movable sections of the hive body where bees build comb and store honey and pollen."&lt;SEP&gt;"Frames are the structural components of the hive that hold the comb and provide a surface for the bees to build their honeycomb and store honey and brood."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-894b591a83b914f8f6e97ef8a4c38432&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ee60400c3602b512e18748159440dc7</data>
