  <data key="d2">chunk-31552e12186e5af657ecc15691569829&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f2370a2f0c089c5553f3263304da90f0</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 57}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WINGS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ANATOMY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Wings are a distinguishing feature of bees, with queens having proportionally shorter wings compared to workers."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f2370a2f0c089c5553f3263304da90f0</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 56}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ABDOMEN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ANATOMY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Abdomen is a part of the bee's body, typically long and tapering in queens."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f2370a2f0c089c5553f3263304da90f0</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 56}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WAX GLANDS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ANATOMY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Wax glands are absent in queens, which are responsible for producing beeswax."&lt;SEP&gt;"Wax glands are specialized structures in bees that secrete wax, which is used to build comb."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cd3280f423032e87d8241124c131edc6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f2370a2f0c089c5553f3263304da90f0</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 56}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STINGER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ANATOMY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Stinger is present in queens, though rarely used."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f2370a2f0c089c5553f3263304da90f0</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 56}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;THROAT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ANATOMY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Throat is the area that can benefit from the use of general teas and honey."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f2370a2f0c089c5553f3263304da90f0</data>
