</node>
<node id="&quot;WORKER BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Worker Bee is a type of bee that does not lay eggs but performs various tasks within the hive, such as caring for larvae and producing beeswax."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-81ecf165e861b9b15f524411477efffe</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 64}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DRONE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Drone is a male bee that mates with the queen and does not lay eggs or perform other tasks within the hive."&lt;SEP&gt;"Drone refers to a specific caste within a bee colony, characterized by its short lifespan, bulkiness, and primary role of mating with a queen."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-31552e12186e5af657ecc15691569829&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81ecf165e861b9b15f524411477efffe</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 67}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEESWAX&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Beeswax is produced by worker bees and used for constructing honeycomb cells in the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-81ecf165e861b9b15f524411477efffe</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 65}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ROYAL JELLY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Royal Jelly is a substance produced by worker bees specifically for feeding the queen and developing larvae into queens."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-81ecf165e861b9b15f524411477efffe</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 65}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LARVA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Larva is the immature stage of the queen bee's development before it forms a cocoon and becomes a pupa."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-81ecf165e861b9b15f524411477efffe</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 64}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PUPA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pupa is the stage in the queen bee's development where it undergoes transformation inside the cocoon before emerging as an adult."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-81ecf165e861b9b15f524411477efffe</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 64}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HONEYCOMB CELLS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Honeycomb Cells are structures built by worker bees using Beeswax, providing storage for honey and brood."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-81ecf165e861b9b15f524411477efffe</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 65}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MATINGS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Matings refer to the process where Drones mate with the Queen Bee, ensuring the genetic diversity of the colony."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-81ecf165e861b9b15f524411477efffe</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 67}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SPERM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sperm is the genetic material carried by the Drones that the Queen Bee stores for future egg-laying."&lt;SEP&gt;"Sperm is the reproductive material carried by the drone for the queen to use in laying eggs."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-31552e12186e5af657ecc15691569829&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81ecf165e861b9b15f524411477efffe</data>
