<node id="&quot;NEW YORK CITY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"New York City is a geographical location where theatrical performances, including musical numbers, were increasingly popular during the late 18th and early 19th centuries."&lt;SEP&gt;"New York City is a location where vaudeville productions were popular, with a large audience attending these shows."&lt;SEP&gt;"New York City is a specific urban center where vaudeville was popular, with large audiences attending performances weekly."&lt;SEP&gt;"New York City is the location where William Henry Brown opened his pleasure garden and later expanded into the American Theatre on Mercer Street."</data>
