</node>
<node id="&quot;SURGERY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Surgery can lead to a loss of saliva production, which is a condition treated by some medications."&lt;SEP&gt;"Surgery is a medical procedure that can lead to a loss of saliva production, necessitating the use of medications or mucalytic agents for treatment."&lt;SEP&gt;"Surgery is a medical procedure that can lead to a loss of saliva production, necessitating the use of medications or mucalytic agents."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-606dabdb846969f5b54692a4eb6683c6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1cebf4db38eecdcd922e057804d86a7c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RADIATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Radiation can also cause a loss of saliva production, another condition treated by some medications."&lt;SEP&gt;"Radiation therapy can cause a loss of saliva production, requiring the use of medications or mucalytic agents for treatment."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-606dabdb846969f5b54692a4eb6683c6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1cebf4db38eecdcd922e057804d86a7c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SALIVA PRODUCTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Saliva production is a physiological function that can be affected by certain conditions or treatments."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-606dabdb846969f5b54692a4eb6683c6</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MUCALYTIC AGENTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Mucalytic Agents are drugs used to thin secretions as needed, often prescribed for singers experiencing persistent laryngeal dryness."&lt;SEP&gt;"Mucalytic agents are drugs used to thin secretions, such as mucus."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-606dabdb846969f5b54692a4eb6683c6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1cebf4db38eecdcd922e057804d86a7c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MEDICATIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Medications refer to drugs formulated to increase saliva production or alter the viscosity of mucus, often used medically to treat patients with reduced saliva production due to surgery or radiation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1cebf4db38eecdcd922e057804d86a7c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OTOLARYNGOLOGIST&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"An Otolaryngologist is a medical professional who can provide a professional opinion on laryngeal dryness and recommend appropriate treatments."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1cebf4db38eecdcd922e057804d86a7c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PHYSICAL ATHLETES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Physical Athletes are individuals who engage in sports and physical activities, benefiting from cardiovascular and strength training."&lt;SEP&gt;"Physical Athletes include vocal performers who engage in various levels of physical activity, from light movement to high-intensity choreography, to maintain cardiovascular fitness and muscular strength."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1cebf4db38eecdcd922e057804d86a7c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ecf136ab47a1a916ed1db34bafaa8f26</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CARDIOVASCULAR TRAINING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cardiovascular Training is a type of exercise that improves heart and lung function, essential for vocal performers to avoid compromising their vocal systems."&lt;SEP&gt;"Cardiovascular Training refers to a type of physical exercise that improves the efficiency of the heart and lungs, beneficial for physical athletes but less common for vocal performers."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1cebf4db38eecdcd922e057804d86a7c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ecf136ab47a1a916ed1db34bafaa8f26</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STRENGTH TRAINING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Strength Training involves exercises designed to improve muscular strength and endurance, also beneficial for physical athletes but less common for vocal performers."&lt;SEP&gt;"Strength Training is a type of exercise that builds muscle mass and strength, important for vocal performers to maintain overall physical fitness."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1cebf4db38eecdcd922e057804d86a7c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ecf136ab47a1a916ed1db34bafaa8f26</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OPERATIC STAGE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Operatic Stage is a setting where vocal performances take place, typically requiring less physical activity compared to other performance settings."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1cebf4db38eecdcd922e057804d86a7c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;POP STAR ARENA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Pop Star Arena is a setting where vocal performances take place, often requiring higher levels of physical activity compared to the operatic stage."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1cebf4db38eecdcd922e057804d86a7c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VOCAL PERFORMERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vocal Performers are individuals who engage in singing performances, often requiring mental focus and toughness, and may require additional support for mental wellness."&lt;SEP&gt;"Vocal Performers are individuals who engage in singing, whether in a recital, choral setting, or on a pop star arena, and require both physical and mental wellness to perform optimally."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1cebf4db38eecdcd922e057804d86a7c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ecf136ab47a1a916ed1db34bafaa8f26</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MENTAL FOCUS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Mental Focus is the ability to concentrate and maintain a sharp mind during performances, crucial for vocal performers."&lt;SEP&gt;"Mental Focus is the ability to concentrate and stay focused, crucial for vocal performers during performances and auditions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1cebf4db38eecdcd922e057804d86a7c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ecf136ab47a1a916ed1db34bafaa8f26</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MENTAL TOUGHNESS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Mental Toughness is the ability to maintain composure and resilience under pressure, important for vocal performers during auditions and training."&lt;SEP&gt;"Mental Toughness is the resilience and determination to handle the stress and pressure of auditions and performances, vital for vocal performers."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1cebf4db38eecdcd922e057804d86a7c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ecf136ab47a1a916ed1db34bafaa8f26</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RECITAL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Recital is a performance setting where vocalists may perform, typically requiring less physical activity compared to other performance settings."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1cebf4db38eecdcd922e057804d86a7c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CHORAL SETTING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Choral Setting is a performance setting where vocalists may perform, often involving group singing and varying levels of physical activity."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1cebf4db38eecdcd922e057804d86a7c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BREATHLESSNESS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Breathlessness is a condition that can result from compensatory vocal behaviors and can affect vocal performance."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1cebf4db38eecdcd922e057804d86a7c</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 10}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 70}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COMPENSATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Compensation is a behavior where the larynx attempts to regulate air flow due to breathlessness, which can lead to changes in vocal performance over time."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1cebf4db38eecdcd922e057804d86a7c</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 10}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 70}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ACROBATICS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Acrobatics are physical movements that may be included in the range of physical activity for vocal performers, increasing their onstage physical activity level."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1cebf4db38eecdcd922e057804d86a7c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PERFORMANCE CULTURE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Performance Culture refers to the environment and expectations surrounding vocal performances, which can influence the physical demands placed on performers."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1cebf4db38eecdcd922e057804d86a7c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PROFESSIONAL OPINION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Professional Opinion is advice given by a medical professional, such as an Otolaryngologist, to address laryngeal dryness and other vocal issues."</data>
