  <data key="d6">chunk-4c3eb78a029c96288b495cbd85393985</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ELTON&quot;" target="&quot;200-PAGE BOOK&quot;">
  <data key="d4">20.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Elton is the author of the 200-page book, which focuses on the new science of ecology and the sociology and economics of animals."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-6f20e95f2b687a8963c77f9d1f946da0</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ELTON&quot;" target="&quot;CARL LINNAEUS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Elton's work on the sociology and economics of animals builds upon the concept of an 'economy of nature,' which was previously embraced by Carl Linnaeus in the eighteenth century."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-6f20e95f2b687a8963c77f9d1f946da0</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ELTON&quot;" target="&quot;DARWIN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Elton's ideas on the sociology and economics of animals are also influenced by Charles Darwin's embrace of the 'economy of nature' in the nineteenth century."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-6f20e95f2b687a8963c77f9d1f946da0</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ELTON&quot;" target="&quot;ENGAGING, CONVERSATIONAL TONE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Elton uses an engaging, conversational tone in his book to make complex ideas accessible to readers."</data>
