  <data key="d5">"Elton explores the southern portion of the twelve-mile-long island with the landing party."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-6dcaa3fb65de0bc40334b1db91763464</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ELTON&quot;" target="&quot;VINCENT SUMMERHAYES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Vincent Summerhayes works alongside Elton to survey all plants and other animals on the island."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-6dcaa3fb65de0bc40334b1db91763464</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ELTON&quot;" target="&quot;ORNITHOLOGISTS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">5.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The ornithologists in the group focus on studying the birdlife on the island, separate from Elton's and Summerhayes' work."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-6dcaa3fb65de0bc40334b1db91763464</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ELTON&quot;" target="&quot;ORNITHOLOGISTS GROUP&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Elton is part of the Ornithologists Group, focusing on birdlife during the expedition."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-20e38e48ffc37fb717229a5dc03ff3a9</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ELTON&quot;" target="&quot;F.C.R. JOURDAIN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"F.C.R. Jourdain is the leader of the expedition and commands Elton, but Elton learns to heed Longstaff's advice instead due to exhaustion concerns."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-20e38e48ffc37fb717229a5dc03ff3a9</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ELTON&quot;" target="&quot;LONGSTAFF&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Longstaff advises Elton to ignore F.C.R. Jourdain's commands due to exhaustion concerns, and Elton appreciates this advice."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-20e38e48ffc37fb717229a5dc03ff3a9</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;JULIAN HUXLEY&quot;" target="&quot;_ANIMAL ECOLOGY_&quot;">
  <data key="d4">23.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Julian Huxley facilitated the creation of the book _Animal Ecology_ by proposing it to Elton."&lt;SEP&gt;"Julian Huxley played a role in proposing and facilitating the creation of the book _Animal Ecology_."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-4c3eb78a029c96288b495cbd85393985</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;JULIAN HUXLEY&quot;" target="&quot;SHORT BOOKS ON BIOLOGY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Julian Huxley was involved in the series of short books on biology, proposing a book on animal ecology for this series."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-4c3eb78a029c96288b495cbd85393985</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;JULIAN HUXLEY&quot;" target="&quot;SPITSBERGEN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Julian Huxley led the expedition to Spitsbergen, a remote Arctic island, for the purpose of conducting natural history research."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8cac479cb6cdd8c93500916fa7e3e364</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;JULIAN HUXLEY&quot;" target="&quot;OXFORD UNIVERSITY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Julian Huxley, an eminent zoologist and writer, was invited by Oxford University to lead the expedition."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8cac479cb6cdd8c93500916fa7e3e364</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ARCTIC&quot;" target="&quot;200-PAGE BOOK&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Arctic is a location where Elton conducted studies for his book, emphasizing the importance of food and food chains in animal communities."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-6f20e95f2b687a8963c77f9d1f946da0</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
