  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The island provides habitat for the black and white Common and Brunnich's guillemots, which swarm in large numbers on its southern cliffs."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5b8998c07aafc0d539e88b3e51f159fe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;THE ISLAND&quot;" target="&quot;HONEY BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"While not explicitly located on the island, honey bees are mentioned in relation to swarming, a concept that parallels the island's natural phenomena."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5b8998c07aafc0d539e88b3e51f159fe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;THE ISLAND&quot;" target="&quot;SWARMING&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The island's seabirds engage in swarming behavior, which is a natural phenomenon observed there."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5b8998c07aafc0d539e88b3e51f159fe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
