  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Polar Current contributes to the harsh weather conditions on the Island, where the expedition takes place."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-20e38e48ffc37fb717229a5dc03ff3a9</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ISLAND&quot;" target="&quot;GULF STREAM&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Gulf Stream meets the Polar Current near the Island, affecting its climate and weather patterns."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-20e38e48ffc37fb717229a5dc03ff3a9</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ISLAND&quot;" target="&quot;LAKES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Lakes are numerous bodies of water found throughout the interior of the Island, contributing to its geography and providing habitats for wildlife."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-20e38e48ffc37fb717229a5dc03ff3a9</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ISLAND&quot;" target="&quot;COVER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Cover refers to the natural vegetation and terrain that provides shelter and habitat for wildlife on the Island, which the birders aim to study."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-20e38e48ffc37fb717229a5dc03ff3a9</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SLEET&quot;" target="&quot;WEATHER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Sleet is a form of precipitation that occurs during the expedition, contributing to the harsh weather conditions on the Island."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-20e38e48ffc37fb717229a5dc03ff3a9</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BLIZZARDS&quot;" target="&quot;WEATHER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Blizzards are severe snowstorms that occur frequently on the Island during the expedition, contributing to the harsh weather conditions."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-20e38e48ffc37fb717229a5dc03ff3a9</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HONEY BEES&quot;" target="&quot;SWARMING&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Honey bees undergo swarming as a means of colony reproduction and survival, similar to the seabirds on the island."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5b8998c07aafc0d539e88b3e51f159fe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HONEY BEES&quot;" target="&quot;COLONIES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Honey bees live in colonies that can potentially achieve immortality through swarming, paralleling the island's natural processes."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5b8998c07aafc0d539e88b3e51f159fe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TALL CLIFFS&quot;" target="&quot;SEABIRDS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Seabirds, including black and white Common and Brunnich's guillemots, swarm in large numbers on the island's southern cliffs."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5b8998c07aafc0d539e88b3e51f159fe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;DISEASE&quot;" target="&quot;COLONIES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Disease can cause colonies to die, affecting the health and survival of honey bee colonies."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5b8998c07aafc0d539e88b3e51f159fe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;FIRE&quot;" target="&quot;COLONIES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Fire can cause colonies to die, affecting the health and survival of honey bee colonies."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5b8998c07aafc0d539e88b3e51f159fe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PREDATORS&quot;" target="&quot;COLONIES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Predators can cause colonies to die, affecting the health and survival of honey bee colonies."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5b8998c07aafc0d539e88b3e51f159fe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NATURAL DISASTERS&quot;" target="&quot;COLONIES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Natural disasters can cause colonies to die, affecting the health and survival of honey bee colonies."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5b8998c07aafc0d539e88b3e51f159fe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;UNNATURAL DISASTERS&quot;" target="&quot;COLONIES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Unnatural disasters can cause colonies to die, affecting the health and survival of honey bee colonies."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5b8998c07aafc0d539e88b3e51f159fe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PARENT COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;SWARMING&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A parent colony of honey bees is the source from which swarming occurs, splitting into a new colony."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5b8998c07aafc0d539e88b3e51f159fe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PARENT COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees form the Parent Colony, which includes the queen and worker bees, and can initiate the swarm process."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-21b0db176175776d50cdbbd4696b062b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PARENT COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;SURVIVAL&quot;">
  <data key="d4">21.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Survival is crucial for both the swarm and the parent colony, especially during winter."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-21b0db176175776d50cdbbd4696b062b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PARENT COLONY&quot;" target="&quot;REESTABLISHMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Reestablishment is necessary for the parent colony to regain its strength after a swarm."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-21b0db176175776d50cdbbd4696b062b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;QUEEN BEE&quot;" target="&quot;SWARM&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Queen Bee initiates the swarm process by leaving the hive with a portion of the colony."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-21b0db176175776d50cdbbd4696b062b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;QUEEN BEE&quot;" target="&quot;WORKER BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Queen Bee is the mother of all worker bees and plays a critical role in the colony's survival and reproduction."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-81ecf165e861b9b15f524411477efffe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;QUEEN BEE&quot;" target="&quot;DRONE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">36.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Drones mate with the Queen Bee during Mating Flights, ensuring the genetic diversity of the colony."&lt;SEP&gt;"Drones mate with the Queen Bee during their mating flights, ensuring the genetic diversity of the colony."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Queen Bee mates with Drones to produce offspring, ensuring the continuation of the colony."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-81ecf165e861b9b15f524411477efffe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;QUEEN BEE&quot;" target="&quot;BEESWAX&quot;">
  <data key="d4">5.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Queen Bee does not produce Beeswax, but worker bees use it for constructing honeycomb cells."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-81ecf165e861b9b15f524411477efffe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;QUEEN BEE&quot;" target="&quot;ROYAL JELLY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Queen Bee is fed Royal Jelly exclusively during her larval stage, which is essential for her development into a queen."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-81ecf165e861b9b15f524411477efffe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;QUEEN BEE&quot;" target="&quot;LARVA&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Queen Bee develops from a Larva, which is fed Royal Jelly and eventually forms a Pupa."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-81ecf165e861b9b15f524411477efffe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;QUEEN BEE&quot;" target="&quot;PUPA&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Queen Bee transforms into a Pupa after the larval stage, which then matures into an adult Queen."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-81ecf165e861b9b15f524411477efffe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;QUEEN BEE&quot;" target="&quot;HONEYCOMB CELLS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Worker Bees build Honeycomb Cells using Beeswax, which the Queen Bee uses for storing eggs and brood."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-81ecf165e861b9b15f524411477efffe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;QUEEN BEE&quot;" target="&quot;WORKER BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Queen Bee relies on Worker Bees for tasks such as caring for larvae and producing beeswax."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-81ecf165e861b9b15f524411477efffe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;QUEEN BEE&quot;" target="&quot;MATINGS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Queen Bee engages in Matings with Drones to ensure the genetic diversity of the colony."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-81ecf165e861b9b15f524411477efffe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;QUEEN BEE&quot;" target="&quot;SPERM&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Queen Bee stores Sperm from the Drones for future egg-laying."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-81ecf165e861b9b15f524411477efffe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;QUEEN BEE&quot;" target="&quot;MATING FLIGHTS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Queen Bee goes on Mating Flights to mate with multiple Drones."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-81ecf165e861b9b15f524411477efffe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;QUEEN BEE&quot;" target="&quot;COLONY MORALE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Queen Bee's presence maintains Colony Morale within the hive."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-81ecf165e861b9b15f524411477efffe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;QUEEN BEE&quot;" target="&quot;HONEY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Honey is stored in the Honeycomb Cells, which are built by Worker Bees and used by the Queen Bee."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-81ecf165e861b9b15f524411477efffe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;QUEEN BEE&quot;" target="&quot;LARVAE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Queen Bee lays Eggs that develop into Larvae, which are cared for by Worker Bees."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-81ecf165e861b9b15f524411477efffe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;QUEEN BEE&quot;" target="&quot;CELL&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Eggs are laid in Cells within the honeycomb, which are built by Worker Bees."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-81ecf165e861b9b15f524411477efffe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;QUEEN BEE&quot;" target="&quot;MATURE QUEEN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"After completing her development, the Larva matures into a Mature Queen."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-81ecf165e861b9b15f524411477efffe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
