  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;WORKER BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees include worker bees, drones, and the queen in the hive."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-51f25ad8710ba3aff4a2bd9ece017fba</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SWARM&quot;" target="&quot;LATE SPRING AND EARLY SUMMER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The primary swarm season occurs during Late Spring and Early Summer, with about 80 percent of swarms happening during this period."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-21b0db176175776d50cdbbd4696b062b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SWARM&quot;" target="&quot;AUGUST&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The secondary swarm season begins in August, accounting for the remaining 20 percent of swarms."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-21b0db176175776d50cdbbd4696b062b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SWARM&quot;" target="&quot;LOCAL BEEKEEPERS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">5.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Local Beekeepers can provide information about the approximate swarm season for a specific area."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-21b0db176175776d50cdbbd4696b062b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SWARM&quot;" target="&quot;PRIMARY SWARM SEASON&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Primary Swarm Season is the main period for swarming, with about 80 percent of swarms occurring during this time."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-21b0db176175776d50cdbbd4696b062b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SWARM&quot;" target="&quot;SECONDARY SWARM SEASON&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Secondary Swarm Season is a less well-known period for swarming, accounting for the remaining 20 percent of swarms."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-21b0db176175776d50cdbbd4696b062b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SWARM&quot;" target="&quot;PROPAGATING THE SPECIES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">21.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Propagating the Species is the general reason for swarming, ensuring the continuation of the bee population."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-21b0db176175776d50cdbbd4696b062b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;WINTER&quot;" target="&quot;DRONE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Drones do not survive the winter, marking the end of their active season."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-31552e12186e5af657ecc15691569829</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;FORAGING&quot;" target="&quot;ACTIVITY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Foraging is an activity observed during the inspection to check the bees' behavior."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-51f25ad8710ba3aff4a2bd9ece017fba</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SWARMING&quot;" target="&quot;EVENT&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Swarming is a natural process for honey bee colonies and is compared to the island's seabirds swarming, suggesting a parallel phenomenon."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5b8998c07aafc0d539e88b3e51f159fe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;QUEEN&quot;" target="&quot;QUEEN CAGE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The queen cage houses the queen bee temporarily, allowing for controlled movement and inspection of the hive."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8ee60400c3602b512e18748159440dc7</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
