  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The queen lays eggs, producing brood, which is cared for by worker bees within the hive."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8ee60400c3602b512e18748159440dc7</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;QUEEN&quot;" target="&quot;BROOD NEST&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Brood Nest is the area where the Queen lays eggs and the young bees develop."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-894b591a83b914f8f6e97ef8a4c38432</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;QUEEN&quot;" target="&quot;SECOND INSPECTION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Second Inspection checks the progress of the Queen and the overall health of the hive."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-894b591a83b914f8f6e97ef8a4c38432</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;QUEEN&quot;" target="&quot;DRONE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Drones mate with Queens, which is their primary role in the colony."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-31552e12186e5af657ecc15691569829</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;QUEEN&quot;" target="&quot;COLONY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Queens are central to the Colony's survival and growth, as they lay eggs and initiate matings."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-31552e12186e5af657ecc15691569829</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;QUEEN&quot;" target="&quot;PACKAGE COLONY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">28.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Queen is a key component of the Package Colony, whose release and egg-laying process is crucial for the colony's growth."&lt;SEP&gt;"The queen is a critical component of the package colony, essential for the colony's survival and reproduction."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5249d7cd72cb7719eac165e812133b7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3d3ced570c1e921fa39196db14c81607</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;QUEEN&quot;" target="&quot;EGG LAYING&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The process of Egg Laying by the Queen is essential for the growth of the Package Colony."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5249d7cd72cb7719eac165e812133b7</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;QUEEN&quot;" target="&quot;BEEKEEPER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Beekeeper must ensure the release of the Queen to initiate the egg-laying process."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a5249d7cd72cb7719eac165e812133b7</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HIVE&quot;" target="&quot;OUTER COVER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The outer cover is part of the hive structure, protecting the internal components from environmental factors."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8ee60400c3602b512e18748159440dc7</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HIVE&quot;" target="&quot;FRAMES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Frames are integral parts of the hive, providing surfaces for the bees to build comb and store honey and brood."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8ee60400c3602b512e18748159440dc7</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HIVE&quot;" target="&quot;COLONY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Hive is the location where the Colony lives and performs its activities."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-31552e12186e5af657ecc15691569829</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HIVE&quot;" target="&quot;INSPECTION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The inspection takes place at the hive, where the queen and bees are located."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-51f25ad8710ba3aff4a2bd9ece017fba</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;OUTER COVER&quot;" target="&quot;INNER COVER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The inner cover sits between the outer cover and the frames, serving as a protective layer."&lt;SEP&gt;"The outer cover and inner cover work together to protect the frames."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8ee60400c3602b512e18748159440dc7</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;OUTER COVER&quot;" target="&quot;FRAMES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The outer cover, along with the inner cover, protects the frames from environmental factors."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8ee60400c3602b512e18748159440dc7</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;OUTER COVER&quot;" target="&quot;HIVE BODY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Outer Cover protects the Hive Body and the bees inside, providing insulation and protection."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-894b591a83b914f8f6e97ef8a4c38432</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;INNER COVER&quot;" target="&quot;FRAMES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The inner cover protects the frames from direct contact with the outer cover."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8ee60400c3602b512e18748159440dc7</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;INNER COVER&quot;" target="&quot;HIVE BODY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Inner Cover regulates temperature and provides access to the Frames within the Hive Body."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-894b591a83b914f8f6e97ef8a4c38432</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SMOKER&quot;" target="&quot;INSPECTION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The smoker is used to calm the bees during the inspection."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-51f25ad8710ba3aff4a2bd9ece017fba</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
