<edge source="&quot;JOHN KENRICK&quot;" target="&quot;AMERICAN REVOLUTION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"John Kenrick provides historical context on the impact of the American Revolution on theatre in his book 'Musical Theatre: A History'. "</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-bcd11462aef756442e092cdbe53e51fc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;AMERICAN REVOLUTION&quot;" target="&quot;CONTINENTAL CONGRESS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The American Revolution led to the Continental Congress approving a resolution opposing theatre productions, which had a lasting impact on the American stage."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-bcd11462aef756442e092cdbe53e51fc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;AMERICAN REVOLUTION&quot;" target="&quot;STATES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The American Revolution indirectly led to state-level laws banning stage performances, which were in place from 1780 to 1793."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-bcd11462aef756442e092cdbe53e51fc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;AMERICAN REVOLUTION&quot;" target="&quot;THEATRE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The American Revolution had a significant impact on the theatre industry, leading to bans and eventual revivals."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-bcd11462aef756442e092cdbe53e51fc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CONTINENTAL CONGRESS&quot;" target="&quot;STATES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Continental Congress's resolution opposing theatre productions influenced state-level legislation, leading to laws outlawing stage performances."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-bcd11462aef756442e092cdbe53e51fc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PRESIDENT GEORGE WASHINGTON&quot;" target="&quot;STATES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"After the ban on stage performances was lifted, President George Washington's regular theatre attendance helped support the gradual return of stage productions."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-bcd11462aef756442e092cdbe53e51fc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PRESIDENT GEORGE WASHINGTON&quot;" target="&quot;THEATRE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"President George Washington's support for theatre after the American Revolution played a significant role in the revival of stage productions."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-bcd11462aef756442e092cdbe53e51fc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
